title Cold/warm atoms are real Hoon terms — my earlier correction was wrong
prompt Kaeden linked docs.urbit.org/hoon/rune/constants#cold-atom and #warm directly, in response to the prior turn's claim that "cold and warm atoms" was not a real Hoon term and that Kaeden must have meant jet dashboard cold/warm/hot state instead.
think Fetched the linked page directly rather than defending the prior turn's claim. Confirmed immediately: cold atoms ([%rock p=term q=*], a singleton literal type) and warm atoms ([%sand p=term q=*], typed by aura alone) are real, specific, documented Hoon AST-level constant-typing concepts, with no relationship to the jet dashboard's cold/warm/hot state I had substituted in their place.
think Recognized this as my own mistake, not an ambiguity in Kaeden's original phrasing — Kaeden used the correct Urbit term throughout, and I introduced the error by pattern-matching "cold" and "warm" onto a different, similarly-named Urbit concept without checking the specific rune documentation first.
think Corrected external-research/20260713-225841_... directly rather than leaving the error in place with a footnote, since the file was written and committed entirely within this same session and the correction genuinely improves it rather than rewriting settled history. Moved the jet-witness proposal (a real idea on its own merits) out from under the cold/warm-atom heading, since presenting it as an answer to a question about atom typing would have compounded the original mistake rather than only stating it once.
obs The two Urbit concepts share exactly two English words and nothing else -- cold/warm atoms are about constant-type narrowing (singleton vs. general-by-aura); cold/warm/hot state is about jet-driver caching across runtime restarts. Worth remembering as a concrete example of how two genuinely different Urbit ideas can collide in casual language even when neither speaker is being careless.
file external-research/20260713-225841_glow-supplement-scoping-runes-auras-jet-state.md why: corrected in full -- cold/warm atoms now grounded correctly beside the aura discussion; the jet-witness idea kept as its own clearly separate, clearly labeled surface
